tables.table_schema:
CREATE TABLE patterns_and_trends (
    id UUID PRIMARY KEY,
    user_id INT,
    timestamp TIMESTAMP,
    query TEXT,
    result TEXT
);

CREATE TABLE data_science_projects (
    project_id INT PRIMARY KEY,
    project_name VARCHAR(255),
    project_description TEXT,
    project_owner VARCHAR(100),
    project_start_date DATE,
    project_end_date DATE
);

CREATE TABLE analysis_results (
    result_id INT PRIMARY KEY,
    project_id INT,
    analysis_date DATE,
    result_summary TEXT,
    trend_identified VARCHAR(50),
    prediction_accuracy FLOAT,
    FOREIGN KEY (project_id) REFERENCES data_science_projects(project_id)
);

CREATE TABLE large_datasets (
    id INT PRIMARY KEY,
    data TEXT
)

CREATE TABLE patterns (
    id INT PRIMARY KEY,
    pattern_name TEXT,
    pattern_description TEXT
)

CREATE TABLE predictive_analytics (
    id INT PRIMARY KEY,
    query_id INT,
    query_description TEXT
)

CREATE TABLE users (
    user_id INT PRIMARY KEY,
    username VARCHAR(50),
    email VARCHAR(100),
    age INT,
    city VARCHAR(50)
);

CREATE TABLE orders (
    order_id INT PRIMARY KEY,
    user_id INT,
    order_date DATE,
    total_amount DECIMAL,
    status VARCHAR(20)
);

CREATE TABLE products (
    product_id INT PRIMARY KEY,
    product_name VARCHAR(50),
    category VARCHAR(50),
    price DECIMAL,
    stock_quantity INT
);

CREATE TABLE transactions (
    transaction_id INT PRIMARY KEY,
    order_id INT,
    product_id INT,
    quantity INT,
    timestamp TIMESTAMP
);
